revisions.description: Add capability for IPv4/IPv6 statistics availability.
Removed the fields arpRetransmitTime and reasmMaxSize.
Added arpCheck in the DhcpClientState enum
Revise definition of IPv4/IPv6 interface status table index.

cie1000IpConfigInterfacesTable.name: cie1000IpConfigInterfacesTable
cie1000IpConfigInterfacesTable.description: This is the IP interface table. When an IP interface is created it can be configured in the other tables found in this MIB.

cie1000IpConfigInterfacesEntry.name: cie1000IpConfigInterfacesEntry
cie1000IpConfigInterfacesEntry.description: Entries in this table represent IP interfaces created on the system

cie1000IpConfigInterfacesIpv4Table.name: cie1000IpConfigInterfacesIpv4Table
cie1000IpConfigInterfacesIpv4Table.description: IPv4 interface configuration table. This table enables IPv4 related configuration of the corresponding IP interface.

cie1000IpConfigInterfacesIpv4Entry.name: cie1000IpConfigInterfacesIpv4Entry
cie1000IpConfigInterfacesIpv4Entry.description: Each entry in this table represents an IP interface.

cie1000IpConfigInterfacesIpv4Active.name: cie1000IpConfigInterfacesIpv4Active
cie1000IpConfigInterfacesIpv4Active.description: Enable IPv4. IPv4 can only be enabled if either the DHCP client is enabled, or a valid address has been configured.

cie1000IpConfigInterfacesIpv4EnableDhcpC.name: cie1000IpConfigInterfacesIpv4EnableDhcpClient
cie1000IpConfigInterfacesIpv4EnableDhcpC.description: Enable IPv4 DHCP client. Note: the DHCP client can only be enabled if there is no conflict in the values of: ipv4Address, prefixSize, and dhcpClientFallbackTimeout.

cie1000IpConfigInterfacesIpv4Ipv4Address.name: cie1000IpConfigInterfacesIpv4Ipv4Address
cie1000IpConfigInterfacesIpv4Ipv4Address.description: IPv4 address. Note: Multiple interfaces may not have overlapping networks.

cie1000IpConfigInterfacesIpv4PrefixSize.name: cie1000IpConfigInterfacesIpv4PrefixSize
cie1000IpConfigInterfacesIpv4PrefixSize.description: Prefix size of the network. Note: Multiple interfaces may not have overlapping networks.

cie1000IpConfigInterfacesIpv4DhcpClientF.name: cie1000IpConfigInterfacesIpv4DhcpClientFallbackTimeout
cie1000IpConfigInterfacesIpv4DhcpClientF.description: DHCP client fallback timer. If DHCP is disabled then this object has no effect. If DHCP is enabled and the fallback timeout value is different from zero, then this timer will stop the DHCP process and assign the ipv4Address to the interface instead.

cie1000IpConfigInterfacesIpv6Table.name: cie1000IpConfigInterfacesIpv6Table
cie1000IpConfigInterfacesIpv6Table.description: IPv6 interface configuration table. This table enables IPv6 related configuration of the corresponding IP interface.

cie1000IpConfigInterfacesIpv6Entry.name: cie1000IpConfigInterfacesIpv6Entry
cie1000IpConfigInterfacesIpv6Entry.description: Each entry in this table represents an IP interface.

cie1000IpConfigInterfacesIpv6Active.name: cie1000IpConfigInterfacesIpv6Active
cie1000IpConfigInterfacesIpv6Active.description: Enable the static configured IPv6 address. The static configured IPv6 address can only be configured if a valid address has been written into 'ipv6Address' and 'prefixSize'.

cie1000IpConfigRoutesIpv4Table.name: cie1000IpConfigRoutesIpv4Table
cie1000IpConfigRoutesIpv4Table.description: This is the IPv4 route configuration table.

cie1000IpConfigRoutesIpv4Entry.name: cie1000IpConfigRoutesIpv4Entry
cie1000IpConfigRoutesIpv4Entry.description: Each entry in this table represents a configured route. Note: a route may be configured without being active.

cie1000IpConfigRoutesIpv6Table.name: cie1000IpConfigRoutesIpv6Table
cie1000IpConfigRoutesIpv6Table.description: This is the IPv6 route configuration table.

cie1000IpConfigRoutesIpv6Entry.name: cie1000IpConfigRoutesIpv6Entry
cie1000IpConfigRoutesIpv6Entry.description: Each entry in this table represents a configured route. Note: a route may be configured without being active.

cie1000IpConfigRoutesIpv6NextHopInterfac.name: cie1000IpConfigRoutesIpv6NextHopInterface
cie1000IpConfigRoutesIpv6NextHopInterfac.description: If the next-hop address is a link-local address, then the interface of the link-local address must be specified here. Otherwise this value is not used.

cie1000IpConfigRoutesIpv6RowEditorNextHo.name: cie1000IpConfigRoutesIpv6RowEditorNextHopInterface
cie1000IpConfigRoutesIpv6RowEditorNextHo.description: If the next-hop address is a link-local address, then the interface of the link-local address must be specified here. Otherwise this value is not used.

cie1000IpStatusGlobalsIpv4NeighbourTable.name: cie1000IpStatusGlobalsIpv4NeighbourTable

cie1000IpStatusGlobalsIpv4NeighbourInter.name: cie1000IpStatusGlobalsIpv4NeighbourInterface

cie1000IpStatusGlobalsIpv6NeighbourMacAd.description: MAC address associated with the IP address

cie1000IpStatusGlobalsIpv6NeighbourInter.name: cie1000IpStatusGlobalsIpv6NeighbourInterface
cie1000IpStatusGlobalsIpv6NeighbourInter.description: Interface the neighbour can be reached on.

cie1000IpStatusInterfacesLinkOsInterface.description: Interface index used by the operating system.

cie1000IpStatusInterfacesLinkNoarp.name: cie1000IpStatusInterfacesLinkNoarp

cie1000IpStatusInterfacesLinkMulticast.name: cie1000IpStatusInterfacesLinkMulticast

cie1000IpStatusInterfacesIpv4Table.description: This table provides IPv4 status information for IP interfaces. If an interface is configured to use a DHCP client, then the address can be found here.

cie1000IpStatusInterfacesIpv4Entry.name: cie1000IpStatusInterfacesIpv4Entry
cie1000IpStatusInterfacesIpv4Entry.description: Each entry in this table represents an IP interface.

cie1000IpStatusInterfacesDhcpClientV4Tab.description: This table provides status on the DHCP client running on a given interface.

cie1000IpStatusInterfacesIpv6Table.name: cie1000IpStatusInterfacesIpv6Table
cie1000IpStatusInterfacesIpv6Table.description: This table provides IPv6 status information for IP interfaces. If an interface is configured to use a DHCP client, then the address can be found here.

cie1000IpStatusInterfacesIpv6Tentative.name: cie1000IpStatusInterfacesIpv6Tentative
cie1000IpStatusInterfacesIpv6Tentative.description: An address whose uniqueness on a link is being verified, prior to its assignment to an interface. A tentative address is not considered assigned to an interface in the usual sense.

cie1000IpStatusInterfacesIpv6Duplicated.name: cie1000IpStatusInterfacesIpv6Duplicated
cie1000IpStatusInterfacesIpv6Duplicated.description: Indicates the address duplication is detected by Duplicate Address Detection (DAD). If the address is a link-local address formed from an interface identifier based on the hardware address, which is supposed to be uniquely assigned (e.g., EUI-64 for an Ethernet interface), IP operation on the interface should be disabled.

cie1000IpStatusInterfacesIpv6Detached.name: cie1000IpStatusInterfacesIpv6Detached
cie1000IpStatusInterfacesIpv6Detached.description: Indicates this address is ready to be detached from the link (IPv6 network).

cie1000IpStatusInterfacesIpv6Nodad.name: cie1000IpStatusInterfacesIpv6Nodad

cie1000IpStatusInterfacesIpv6Autoconf.name: cie1000IpStatusInterfacesIpv6Autoconf
cie1000IpStatusInterfacesIpv6Autoconf.description: Indicates this address is capable of being retrieved by stateless address autoconfiguration.

cie1000IpStatusRoutesIpv6Entry.description: Each entry in this table represents an IP route in the system's routing table.

cie1000IpStatusRoutesIpv6NextHopInterfac.name: cie1000IpStatusRoutesIpv6NextHopInterface

cie1000IpStatusRoutesIpv6FlagHost.name: cie1000IpStatusRoutesIpv6FlagHost
cie1000IpStatusRoutesIpv6FlagHost.description: The route is forwarding to this host (loop-back).

cie1000IpStatusRoutesIpv6FlagGateway.name: cie1000IpStatusRoutesIpv6FlagGateway
cie1000IpStatusRoutesIpv6FlagGateway.description: The route is using a gateway as next-hop, of not set then an interface is used.

cie1000IpStatusRoutesIpv6OwnerConf.description: The route is installed as part of the user configuration.

cie1000IpControlGlobalsIpv6SystemStatist.description: Clear the system-wide IPv6 traffic statistics.

cie1000IpControlInterfaceDhcpClientTable.description: This table provides control facilities to control an instance of the DHCP client.

cie1000IpControlInterfaceDhcpClientEntry.name: cie1000IpControlInterfaceDhcpClientEntry
cie1000IpControlInterfaceDhcpClientEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents an instance of the DHCP client.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InReceives.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InReceives
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InReceives.description: Number of input IP datagrams received, including those received in error. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCInReceiv.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCInReceives
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCInReceiv.description: Number of input IP datagrams received, including those received in error. This object counts the same datagrams as InReceives, but allows for larger values. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InOctets.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InOctets
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InOctets.description: Number of octets received in input IP datagrams, including those received in error. Octets from datagrams counted in InReceives must be counted here. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCInOctets.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCInOctets
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCInOctets.description: Number of octets received in input IP datagrams, including those received in error. This object counts the same octets as InOctets, but allows for a larger value. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InHdrError.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InHdrErrors
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InHdrError.description: Number of input IP datagrams discarded due to errors in their IP headers, including version number mismatch, other format errors, hop count exceeded, and errors discovered in processing their IP options. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InNoRoutes.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InNoRoutes
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InNoRoutes.description: Number of input IP datagrams discarded because no route could be found to transmit them to their destination. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InAddrErro.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InAddrErrors
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InAddrErro.description: Number of input IP datagrams discarded because the IP address in their IP header's destination field was not a valid address to be received at this entity. This count includes invalid addresses (e.g., ::0). For entities that are not IP routers and therefore do not forward datagrams, this counter includes datagrams discarded because the destination address was not a local address. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InUnknownP.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InUnknownProtos
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InUnknownP.description: Number of locally-addressed IP datagrams received successfully but discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol. When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the interface to which these datagrams were addressed is incremented. This interface might not be the same as the input interface for some of the datagrams. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InTruncate.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InTruncatedPkts
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InTruncate.description: Number of input IP datagrams discarded because the datagram frame didn't carry enough data. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InForwData.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InForwDatagrams
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InForwData.description: Number of input datagrams for which this entity was not their final IP destination and for which this entity attempted to find a route to forward them to their final destination. When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the incoming interface is incremented for each datagram. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCInForwDa.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCInForwDatagrams
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCInForwDa.description: Number of input datagrams for which this entity was not their final IP destination and for which this entity attempted to find a route to forward them to their final destination. This object counts the same packets as InForwDatagrams, but allows for larger values. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4ReasmReqds.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4ReasmReqds
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4ReasmReqds.description: Number of IP fragments received that needed to be reassembled at this interface. When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the interface to which these fragments were addressed is incremented. This interface might not be the same as the input interface for some of the fragments. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4ReasmOKs.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4ReasmOKs
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4ReasmOKs.description: Number of IP datagrams successfully reassembled. When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the interface to which these datagrams were addressed is incremented. This interface might not be the same as the input interface for some of the datagrams. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4ReasmFails.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4ReasmFails
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4ReasmFails.description: Number of failures detected by the IP re-assembly algorithm. Note: this is not necessarily a count of discarded IP fragments because some algorithms (notably the algorithm in RFC 815) can lose track of the number of fragments by combining them as they are received. When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the interface to which these fragments were addressed is incremented. This interface might not be the same as the input interface for some of the fragments. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InDiscards.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InDiscards
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InDiscards.description: Number of input IP datagrams for which no problems were encountered to prevent their continued processing, but were discarded. Note: this counter does not include any datagrams discarded while awaiting re-assembly. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InDelivers.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InDelivers
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4InDelivers.description: Number of datagrams successfully delivered to IP user-protocols (including ICMP). When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the interface to which these datagrams were addressed is incremented. This interface might not be the same as the input interface for some of the datagrams. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCInDelive.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCInDelivers
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCInDelive.description: Number of datagrams successfully delivered to IP user-protocols (including ICMP). This object counts the same packets as ipSystemStatsInDelivers, but allows for larger values. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutRequest.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutRequests
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutRequest.description: Number of IP datagrams that local IP user-protocols (including ICMP) supplied to IP in requests for transmission. Note: this counter does not include any datagrams counted in OutForwDatagrams. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCOutReque.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCOutRequests
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCOutReque.description: Number of IP datagrams that local IP user-protocols (including ICMP) supplied to IP in requests for transmission. This object counts the same packets as OutRequests, but allows for larger values. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutNoRoute.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutNoRoutes
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutNoRoute.description: Number of locally generated IP datagrams discarded because no route could be found to transmit them to their destination. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutForwDat.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutForwDatagrams
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutForwDat.description: Number of datagrams for which this entity was not their final IP destination and for which it was successful in finding a path to their final destination. When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the outgoing interface is incremented for a successfully forwarded datagram. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCOutForwD.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCOutForwDatagrams
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4HCOutForwD.description: Number of datagrams for which this entity was not their final IP destination and for which it was successful in finding a path to their final destination. This object counts the same packets as OutForwDatagrams, but allows for larger values. cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutDiscard.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutDiscards

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutFragReq.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutFragReqds

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutFragOKs.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutFragOKs

Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutFragCre.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4OutFragCreates

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4RefreshRat.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4RefreshRate
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv4RefreshRat.description: The minimum reasonable polling interval for this entry. This object provides an indication of the minimum amount of time required to update the counters in this entry.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6HCInOctets.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6HCInOctets
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6HCInOctets.description: Number of octets received in input IP datagrams, including those received in error. This object counts the same octets as InOctets, but allows for a larger value. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InHdrError.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InHdrErrors
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InHdrError.description: Number of input IP datagrams discarded due to errors in their IP headers, including version number mismatch, other format errors, hop count exceeded, and errors discovered in processing their IP options. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InNoRoutes.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InNoRoutes
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InNoRoutes.description: Number of input IP datagrams discarded because no route could be found to transmit them to their destination. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InAddrErro.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InAddrErrors
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InAddrErro.description: Number of input IP datagrams discarded because the IP address in their IP header's destination field was not a valid address to be received at this entity. This count includes invalid addresses (e.g., ::0). For entities that are not IP routers and therefore do not forward datagrams, this counter includes datagrams discarded because the destination address was not a local address. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InUnknownP.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InUnknownProtos
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InUnknownP.description: Number of locally-addressed IP datagrams received successfully but discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol. When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the interface to which these datagrams were addressed is incremented. This interface might not be the same as the input interface for some of the datagrams. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InTruncate.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InTruncatedPkts
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InTruncate.description: Number of input IP datagrams discarded because the datagram frame didn't carry enough data. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InForwData.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InForwDatagrams
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InForwData.description: Number of input datagrams for which this entity was not their final IP destination and for which this entity attempted to find a route to forward them to their final destination. When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the incoming interface is incremented for each datagram. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6HCInForwDa.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6HCInForwDatagrams

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6ReasmReqds.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6ReasmReqds

When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the interface to which these fragments were addressed is incremented. This interface might not be the same as the input interface for some of the fragments. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6ReasmOKs.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6ReasmOKs

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6ReasmFails.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6ReasmFails

Note: this is not necessarily a count of discarded IP fragments because some algorithms (notably the algorithm in RFC 815) can lose track of the number of fragments by combining them as they are received. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InDelivers.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6InDelivers

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6HCInBcastP.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6HCInBcastPkts
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6HCInBcastP.description: Number of IP broadcast datagrams received. This object counts the same datagrams as InBcastPkts but allows for larger values. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6OutBcastPk.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6OutBcastPkts
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6OutBcastPk.description: Number of IP broadcast datagrams transmitted. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6HCOutBcast.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6HCOutBcastPkts
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6HCOutBcast.description: Number of IP broadcast datagrams transmitted. This object counts the same datagrams as OutBcastPkts, but allows for larger values. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6Discontinu.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6DiscontinuityTime
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6Discontinu.description: Value of sysUpTime on the most recent occasion when any one or more of this entry's counters suffered a discontinuity. If no such discontinuities have occurred since the last re-initialization of the IP stack, then this object contains a zero value.

cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6RefreshRat.name: cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6RefreshRate
cie1000IpStatisticsGlobalsIpv6RefreshRat.description: The minimum reasonable polling interval for this entry. This object provides an indication of the minimum amount of time required to update the counters in this entry.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesLinkTable.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesLinkTable
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesLinkTable.description: This table provides interface link statistics for a given IP interface.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesLinkEntry.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesLinkEntry
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesLinkEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents an IP interface.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesLinkInPacke.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesLinkInPackets
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesLinkInPacke.description: Number of packets delivered by MAC layer to IP layer.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesLinkOutPack.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesLinkOutPackets
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesLinkOutPack.description: Number of packets IP protocols requested be transmitted, including those that were discarded or not sent.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesLinkInBytes.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesLinkInBytes
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesLinkInBytes.description: Number of octets received on the interface, including framing characters.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesLinkOutByte.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesLinkOutBytes
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesLinkOutByte.description: Number of octets transmitted out of the interface, including framing characters.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesLinkInMulti.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesLinkInMulticasts
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesLinkInMulti.description: Number of packets delivered by MAC layer to IP layer that were addressed to a MAC multicast address. For a MAC layer protocol, this includes both Group and Functional addresses.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesLinkOutMult.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesLinkOutMulticasts
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesLinkOutMult.description: Number of packets addressed to a multicast MAC address that IP protocols requested be transmitted, including those that were discarded or not sent. For a MAC layer protocol, this includes both Group and Functional addresses.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesLinkInBroad.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesLinkInBroadcasts
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesLinkInBroad.description: Number of packets delivered by MAC layer to IP layer that were addressed to a MAC broadcast address.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesLinkOutBroa.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesLinkOutBroadcasts
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesLinkOutBroa.description: Number of packets addressed to a broadcast MAC address that IP protocols requested be transmitted, including those that were discarded or not sent.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4Table.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4Table
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4Table.description: This table provides IPv4 related statitics for a given IP interface.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4Entry.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4Entry
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4Entry.description: Each entry in this table represents an IP interface.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4IfIndex.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4IfIndex
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4IfIndex.description: Interface index number. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InRecei.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InReceives
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InRecei.description: Number of input IP datagrams received, including those received in error. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCInRec.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCInReceives
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCInRec.description: Number of input IP datagrams received, including those received in error. This object counts the same datagrams as InReceives, but allows for larger values. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InOctet.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InOctets
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InOctet.description: Number of octets received in input IP datagrams, including those received in error. Octets from datagrams counted in InReceives must be counted here. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCInOct.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCInOctets
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCInOct.description: Number of octets received in input IP datagrams, including those received in error. This object counts the same octets as InOctets, but allows for a larger value. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InHdrEr.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InHdrErrors
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InHdrEr.description: Number of input IP datagrams discarded due to errors in their IP headers, including version number mismatch, other format errors, hop count exceeded, and errors discovered in processing their IP options. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InNoRou.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InNoRoutes
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InNoRou.description: Number of input IP datagrams discarded because no route could be found to transmit them to their destination. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InAddrE.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InAddrErrors
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InAddrE.description: Number of input IP datagrams discarded because the IP address in their IP header's destination field was not a valid address to be received at this entity. This count includes invalid addresses (e.g., ::0). For entities that are not IP routers and therefore do not forward datagrams, this counter includes datagrams discarded because the destination address was not a local address. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InUnkno.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InUnknownProtos
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InUnkno.description: Number of locally-addressed IP datagrams received successfully but discarded because of an unknown or unsupported protocol. When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the interface to which these datagrams were addressed is incremented. This interface might not be the same as the input interface for some of the datagrams. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InTrunc.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InTruncatedPkts
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InTrunc.description: Number of input IP datagrams discarded because the datagram frame didn't carry enough data. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InForwD.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InForwDatagrams
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InForwD.description: Number of input datagrams for which this entity was not their final IP destination and for which this entity attempted to find a route to forward them to their final destination. When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the incoming interface is incremented for each datagram. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCInFor.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCInForwDatagrams
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCInFor.description: Number of input datagrams for which this entity was not their final IP destination and for which this entity attempted to find a route to forward them to their final destination. This object counts the same packets as InForwDatagrams, but allows for larger values. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4ReasmRe.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4ReasmReqds
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4ReasmRe.description: Number of IP fragments received that needed to be reassembled at this interface. When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the interface to which these fragments were addressed is incremented. This interface might not be the same as the input interface for some of the fragments. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4ReasmOK.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4ReasmOKs
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4ReasmOK.description: Number of IP datagrams successfully reassembled. When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the interface to which these datagrams were addressed is incremented. This interface might not be the same as the input interface for some of the datagrams. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4ReasmFa.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4ReasmFails
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4ReasmFa.description: Number of failures detected by the IP re-assembly algorithm. Note: this is not necessarily a count of discarded IP fragments because some algorithms (notably the algorithm in RFC 815) can lose track of the number of fragments by combining them as they are received. When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the interface to which these fragments were addressed is incremented. This interface might not be the same as the input interface for some of the fragments. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InDisca.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InDiscards
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InDisca.description: Number of input IP datagrams for which no problems were encountered to prevent their continued processing, but were discarded. Note: this counter does not include any datagrams discarded while awaiting re-assembly. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InDeliv.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InDelivers
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InDeliv.description: Number of datagrams successfully delivered to IP user-protocols (including ICMP). When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the interface to which these datagrams were addressed is incremented. This interface might not be the same as the input interface for some of the datagrams. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCInDel.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCInDelivers
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCInDel.description: Number of datagrams successfully delivered to IP user-protocols (including ICMP). This object counts the same packets as ipSystemStatsInDelivers, but allows for larger values. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutRequ.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutRequests
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutRequ.description: Number of IP datagrams that local IP user-protocols (including ICMP) supplied to IP in requests for transmission. Note: this counter does not include any datagrams counted in OutForwDatagrams. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCOutRe.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCOutRequests
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCOutRe.description: Number of IP datagrams that local IP user-protocols (including ICMP) supplied to IP in requests for transmission. This object counts the same packets as OutRequests, but allows for larger values. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutNoRo.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutNoRoutes
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutNoRo.description: Number of locally generated IP datagrams discarded because no route could be found to transmit them to their destination. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutForw.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutForwDatagrams
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutForw.description: Number of datagrams for which this entity was not their final IP destination and for which it was successful in finding a path to their final destination. When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the outgoing interface is incremented for a successfully forwarded datagram. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCOutFo.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCOutForwDatagrams
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCOutFo.description: Number of datagrams for which this entity was not their final IP destination and for which it was successful in finding a path to their final destination. This object counts the same packets as OutForwDatagrams, but allows for larger values. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutDisc.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutDiscards
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutDisc.description: Number of output IP datagrams for which no problem was encountered to prevent their transmission to their destination, but were discarded. Note: this counter includes datagrams counted in OutForwDatagrams if any such datagrams met this (discretionary) discard criterion. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutFrag.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutFragReqds
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutFrag.description: Number of IP datagrams that require fragmentation in order to be transmitted. When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the outgoing interface is incremented for a successfully fragmented datagram. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutFrag.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutFragOKs
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutFrag.description: Number of IP datagrams that have been successfully fragmented. When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the outgoing interface is incremented for a successfully fragmented datagram. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutFrag.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutFragFails
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutFrag.description: Number of IP datagrams that have been discarded because they needed to be fragmented but could not be. This includes IPv4 packets that have the DF bit set and IPv6 packets that are being forwarded and exceed the outgoing link MTU. When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the outgoing interface is incremented for an unsuccessfully fragmented datagram. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutFrag.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutFragCreates
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutFrag.description: Number of output datagram fragments that have been generated as a result of IP fragmentation. When tracking interface statistics, the counter of the outgoing interface is incremented for a successfully fragmented datagram. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutTran.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutTransmits
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutTran.description: Number of IP datagrams that this entity supplied to the lower layers for transmission. This includes datagrams generated locally and those forwarded by this entity. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCOutTr.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCOutTransmits
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCOutTr.description: Number of IP datagrams that this entity supplied to the lower layers for transmission. This object counts the same datagrams as OutTransmits, but allows for larger values. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutOcte.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutOctets
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutOcte.description: Number of octets in IP datagrams delivered to the lower layers for transmission. Octets from datagrams counted in OutTransmits must be counted here. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCOutOc.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCOutOctets
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCOutOc.description: Number of octets in IP datagrams delivered to the lower layers for transmission. This objects counts the same octets as OutOctets, but allows for larger values. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InMcast.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InMcastPkts
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InMcast.description: Number of IP multicast datagrams received. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCInMca.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCInMcastPkts
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCInMca.description: Number of IP multicast datagrams received. This object counts the same datagrams as InMcastPkts but allows for larger values. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InMcast.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InMcastOctets
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InMcast.description: Number of octets received in IP multicast datagrams. Octets from datagrams counted in InMcastPkts MUST be counted here. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCInMca.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCInMcastOctets
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCInMca.description: Number of octets received in IP multicast datagrams. This object counts the same octets as InMcastOctets, but allows for larger values. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutMcas.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutMcastPkts
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutMcas.description: Number of IP multicast datagrams transmitted. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCOutMc.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCOutMcastPkts
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCOutMc.description: Number of IP multicast datagrams transmitted. This object counts the same datagrams as OutMcastPkts, but allows for larger values. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutMcas.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutMcastOctets
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutMcas.description: Number of octets transmitted in IP multicast datagrams. Octets from datagrams counted in OutMcastPkts must be counted here. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCOutMc.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCOutMcastOctets
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCOutMc.description: Number of octets transmitted in IP multicast datagrams. This object counts the same octets as OutMcastOctets, but allows for larger values. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InBcast.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InBcastPkts
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4InBcast.description: Number of IP broadcast datagrams received. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCInBca.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCInBcastPkts
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCInBca.description: Number of IP broadcast datagrams received. This object counts the same datagrams as InBcastPkts but allows for larger values. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutBcas.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutBcastPkts
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4OutBcas.description: Number of IP broadcast datagrams transmitted. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCOutBc.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCOutBcastPkts
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4HCOutBc.description: Number of IP broadcast datagrams transmitted. This object counts the same datagrams as OutBcastPkts, but allows for larger values. Discontinuities in the value of this counter may occur at re-initialization of the system, and at other times as indicated by the value of DiscontinuityTime. This object is only available if the capability object 'cie1000IpCapabilitiesHasPerInterfaceIpv4Statistics' is True.

cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4Discont.name: cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4DiscontinuityTime
cie1000IpStatisticsInterfacesIpv4Discont.description: Value of sysUpTime on the most recent occasion when any one or more of this entry's counters suffered a discontinuity. If no such discontinuities have occurred since the last re-initialization of the IP stack, then this object contains a zero value.
